LAGOS – The police in Lagos have arrested a suspected land-grabbing thug, Ayo Olatuniji. The suspect was arrested on the allegation that he led a team of hoodlums last week to 6th Avenue and Fagbile areas of Amuwo Odofin to unleash mayhem on the residents. Daily Independent investigation revealed that live ammunition was recovered from the suspect following his arrest, while other members of his gang escaped with guns and other dangerous weapons. The suspect was arrested by policemen from Idimu Area Command, following a distressed call that the hoodlums had invaded the area. Other members of the gang, it was gathered, were reportedly being identified by police operatives in the state, who are on their trail Ayo was on Wednesday arraigned before an Ajegunle Magistrate Court on one-count charge of alleged theft and illegal possession of ammunition. Police sources at the Idimu Area Command, said that the suspect claimed to be working for a certain Oluomo and TJ, adding that both have gone into hiding . The police source said, “They are the people disturbing Fagbile area and 6th Avenue in FESTAC and we have been on their trail. “Last Monday, they went there and attack some labourers and took three of them away. “They escaped before we got to the scene.” The police added, “Three days after, they invaded the place again and attempted to wreak havoc but our people were proactive. We stormed the area, arrested AY, but other members of his gang escaped He has named the people he worked for. We have invited them but they have gone into hiding. We will get them and charge them to court too.”